<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-7068] Ivy resolve force mode should be turned off by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7068</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem is introduced by  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6486&quot; title=&quot;fix common classes to work with Avro 1.3 reflection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6486&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6486&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Which have caused a lot of mysterious artifact issues (unable to downgrade or do parallel dev, without wiping out both m2 and ivy caches etc.) wasting countless hours of dev (many people&apos;s) time to track down the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12493555">HADOOP-7068</key>
            <summary>Ivy resolve force mode should be turned off by default</summary>
