                            <comment id="12972675" author="vicaya" created="Fri, 17 Dec 2010 22:28:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch introduced a &quot;force-mode&quot; property which is off by default. Can be turned on with -Dforce-mode=true.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12972677" author="jghoman" created="Fri, 17 Dec 2010 22:34:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;force-mode may not be the best name for the option as it doesn&apos;t say anything about ivy.  How about something like force-ivy-resolution.  More descriptive names are better, even if they are longer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12972681" author="vicaya" created="Fri, 17 Dec 2010 22:58:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about force-resolve (ivy is an impl detail.)? it&apos;s only useful to use with resolvers=internal anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12972684" author="jghoman" created="Fri, 17 Dec 2010 23:04:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m ok with force-resolve&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
